<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP05_Seasons_WeatherTemperature" s="316189">
  <T n="name">0x208A2676<!--String: "Weather & Temperature"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP05\UI\Tutorial\WeatherAndTemp_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fdbd94d491eae5d4</T>
      <T n="text">0xB542BFE<!--String: "Weather is everywhere in the Sims! Depending on the current season and world, you'll see a wide range of weather. From sunny days to stormy rains, your Sims will experience the highs and lows of the ever-changing forecast."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP05\UI\Tutorial\WeatherAndTemp_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fdbd94d491eae5d7</T>
      <T n="text">0x801B78B1<!--String: "Weather influences the current temperature of the world. When it's snowing outside, it's freezing! Likewise, when there's a heatwave going on, it'll be burning hot! Make sure your Sims wear proper clothing for the temperature, or there might be deadly consequences. You can also use the Thermostat object to change the temperature inside your home."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP05\UI\Tutorial\WeatherAndTemp_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:fdbd94d491eae5d6</T>
      <T n="image_console" p="InEP05\UI\Tutorial_controller\WeatherAndTemp_3_controller.png">2f7d0004:00000000:47b037227991af39</T>
      <T n="text">0xFD480856<!--String: "If you ever need to know what the current weather or temperature is, check out the new UI under the time controls. By hovering your mouse over it, you'll get accurate information about the current outdoor conditions."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_EP05_Seasons</E>
  </L>
